  <main class="container">
    <header>
      <h1>Aircraft Pitch Controller</h1>
      <p>
        Design and simulation of a pitch control system for a Boeing 747-400.
      </p>
      <div class="badge-row">
        <span class="badge">Aircraft Dynamics</span>
        <span class="badge">Pitch Control</span>
        <span class="badge">MATLAB / Simulink</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- 1. Overview -->
    <section id="overview">
      <figure class="image-block">
        <img
          src="{{ '/assets/images/747-Wallpaper.jpg' | relative_url }}"
          alt="Boeing 747-400 side view used for pitch controller modeling"
        >
        <figcaption>
          <strong>Boeing 747 Aircraft</strong><br>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
      <h2><span>01</span>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        This project was done as the final groupwork assigment for my System Dynamics class - MAE 3260.
        We designed a ptich controller for a Boeing 747-400 Aircraft by:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          Using publicly available geometric and aerodynamic data to quantify forces acting
          on the aircraft in steady, level cruise at an altitude of 35,000 ft.
        </li>

        <li>
          Deriving the transfer functions governing pitch dynamics using Laplace transforms
          and assembling a state-space model of the aircraft.
        </li>

        <li>
          Developing a MATLAB script to compute all aerodynamic coefficients, stability
          derivatives, and system matrices required for dynamic analysis.
        </li>

        <li>
          Designing and tuning a PID-based pitch controller in Simulink to meet performance
          requirements for stability, overshoot, settling time, and control effort.
        </li>
      </ul>
      
    </section>

    <!-- 2. Simulation & Report -->
    <section id="report">
